<!-- ABOUT FLOODS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>About Floods</h2>
  <p>
    Floods happen when heavy rainfall, overflowing rivers, or poor drainage causes water to cover land
    that is normally dry. Punjab faces frequent flooding due to monsoon rains, river overflow
    (Sutlej, Beas, Ravi, Ghaggar), and urban drainage issues.
  </p>
  <p>
    Low-lying areas in Punjab such as Ropar, Jalandhar, Ferozepur, Patiala, and Gurdaspur are highly vulnerable.
  </p>
</article>

<!-- PREPAREDNESS SECTION -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Preparedness Before a Flood</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep important documents in waterproof bags.</li>
    <li>Prepare an emergency kit with water, food, medicines, flashlight, and radio.</li>
    <li>Know flood shelters and evacuation routes in your locality.</li>
    <li>Move animals and vehicles to higher ground.</li>
    <li>Avoid disposing garbage in drains and rivers.</li>
    <li>Stay updated with IMD and Punjab disaster alerts.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- DOs & DON‚ÄôTs -->
